==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endermic
<hw>En*der"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ in + <?/
skin.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Acting through the skin, or by
direct application to the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Endermic method</b></col>, <cd>that in which the medicine
enters the system through the skin, being applied either to the sound
skin, or to the surface denuded of the cuticle by a
blister.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endermically</ent>⟦br⟧
